    "fi t A ft r JV 1 4 PLAIN DEALER FRIDAY MARCH 14 1919 BY MEAD PUBLISHING CO Official Paper of the City and the County Issued on Friday of Each Week Entered at the Post Office at Cresco Iowa as second class mail matter Oar Des Moines Legislative Letter fl9 J W Jarnagin 4 vDes Moines Iowa March 10 1919 fi 1 Upon the reconvening of the legisla ture after a weeks recess matters of interest and deep concern were rushed in at a rapid rate The first thrill came when a message was received from Gov Harding asking that the two houses meet on Thursday in joint ses sion as he had an important message to present Everyone knew that the matter to be discussed was the pardon f Rathbun at Ida Grove and this an nouncement was of sufficient interest to fill the bouse ehamber to overflowing Not only was the floor of the chamber packed but also the galleries The governors forceful reference to the part Attorney General Havner took in getting Ratbbun into the peniten tiary brought from that official a vig orous rejoinder in the newspapers and it may be said in all truth"
